File: Shudufhadzo Musida was crowned Miss South Africa 2020. Instagram/@official_misssa JOHANNESBURG - Former Miss South Africa 2020 Shudufhadzo Musida continues to raise the South African flag high. Musida has now made it to the top 40 for Miss World. She announced the news on her Twitter account. READ: Shudufhadzo Musida crowned Miss SA 2020 Musida will look to be only the fourth South African to clinch the coveted Miss World crown. The 70th edition of Miss World was postponed in December after a COVID-19 outbreak. The event will still be held in Puerto Rico on 16 March. Former Miss South Africa 2020 Shudufhadzo Musida continues to raise the SA flag high. She has now made it to the top 40 for Miss World. She announced the news on her Twitter account earlier today. #SATonight #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/zfF2EYCFBF